            icon: "presentation",
            durationMins: 5,
            actLabel: "Opening",
            contentBlocks: "[{\"type\": \"context\", \"label\": \"Scene Setup\", \"content\": \"You are presenting to Diana Mercer (CHRO), Priya Okafor (HR Ops Manager), and a room of HR Business Partners and Service Center leads at a mid-to-large wealth management firm managing $180B AUM across 900 financial advisors nationwide. The firm is aggressively recruiting from competing wirehouse firms and needs fast, compliant onboarding to convert recruits before they second-guess the move. The HR service center handles approximately 2,200 cases per month. The audience is business-outcome focused \\u2014 lead with revenue impact, not technology features. Do not open a laptop yet. This is a narrative-only opening.\"}, {\"type\": \"note\", \"label\": \"Pre-Demo Setup\", \"content\": \"Before the demo begins prepare the following staged data: (1) Create a demo financial advisor persona 'Jordan Calloway' as a new hire with a start date 7 days from today, currently in an active Lifecycle Event called 'Financial Advisor Onboarding.' (2) Stage 5 open HR cases in sn_hr_core_case with wealth management themes: a 401k employer match question, a Series 7 exam reimbursement question, a relocation allowance question, a PTO carryover policy question, and a beneficiary change request. (3) Ensure Now Assist for HRSD skills 'HR Case Summarization' and 'Suggested Response' are active and configured for the HR Agent Workspace. (4) Pre-populate the Employee Center with a Knowledge Base called 'Advisor Resources' containing articles on: relocation policy, FINRA registration process, 401k plan summary, PTO policy, and compliance training requirements. Each article should be at least 400 words with realistic firm-specific content. (5) Configure the Lifecycle Event 'Financial Advisor Onboarding' with activities: FINRA U4 filing initiation, Series 7 exam scheduling, Series 66 exam scheduling, FINRA fingerprint submission, compliance training enrollment, IT equipment provisioning, client book transfer initiation, benefits enrollment window, and E&O insurance enrollment. (6) Ensure the AI Agent for HR is active with intents for: PTO balance inquiry, benefits enrollment question, policy lookup, and case routing. (7) Clear browser history and cache on the demo machine before the session.\"}, {\"type\": \"actions\", \"label\": \"Click-by-Click\", \"items\": [\"Do not open the laptop during the opening. Stand at the front of the room.\", \"Ask the audience: 'How long does it take to fully onboard a financial advisor at your firm today, from offer acceptance to first client meeting?' Allow 30 seconds for responses.\", \"State the industry benchmark: 'Across wealth management, the answer is typically 6 to 8 weeks \\u2014 and in that window, the advisor generates zero revenue for the firm.'\", \"Reference a simple mental timeline: Week 1-2 is HR paperwork and system access. Week 3-4 is FINRA U4 filing and registration. Week 5-6 is compliance training and supervision period. Week 7-8 is when the client book transfer begins.\", \"Anchor the revenue cost: 'A typical producing advisor generates $600K to $1.2M in annual revenue. An 8-week onboarding delay costs the firm $90K to $185K per hire in delayed revenue \\u2014 before you account for the risk that the recruit changes their mind.'\", \"Pivot to HR operations: 'Meanwhile your HR service center is fielding the same questions from every new advisor \\u2014 what is my relocation allowance, when will my FINRA registration clear, how does the 401k match work \\u2014 and each of those questions takes 15 to 20 minutes to research and respond to.'\", \"Introduce the session: 'Today I am going to show you how ServiceNow Now Assist for HRSD changes all three of those dynamics \\u2014 advisor self-service so they get answers instantly, HR reps who work faster with more confidence, and an onboarding workflow that runs itself from Day 1.'\"]}, {\"type\": \"talktrack\", \"label\": \"Talk Track\", \"content\": \"Open with a question that surfaces the pain before presenting any solution. Use wealth management language throughout. Avoid technology jargon entirely in this opening segment.\", \"lines\": [{\"persona\": \"You\", \"text\": \"Before I show you anything on a screen, I want to ask a question. How long does it take today \\u2014 from the moment a financial advisor signs their offer letter to the day they sit down with their first client? Weeks? Anyone want to put a number on it?\"}, {\"persona\": \"Diana Mercer\", \"text\": \"Honestly, best case we are at six weeks. More often it is eight or nine if there are any FINRA complications.\"}, {\"persona\": \"You\", \"text\": \"Six to nine weeks. And in that window, what is that advisor doing? They are not generating revenue. They are waiting on HR, waiting on compliance, waiting on IT \\u2014 and every day they wait is a day they wonder if they made the right decision leaving their previous firm. The industry data puts the cost of that delay at roughly $150,000 per hire in delayed revenue before you factor in the cost of a rescind. That is the business case we are solving today. Not an HR efficiency project \\u2014 a revenue acceleration initiative. Let me show you how.\"}]}, {\"type\": \"watchfor\", \"label\": \"Watch For\", \"items\": [\"Heads nodding when you cite the onboarding timeline \\u2014 this confirms the pain is real and validates the demo narrative\", \"CHROs who push back on the timeline as 'not that long for us' \\u2014 if this happens pivot immediately to the HR case volume angle instead\", \"HR reps in the room making eye contact when you describe repetitive case questions \\u2014 they are your champions; note them for engagement during Act 2\", \"Anyone checking their phone during the opening \\u2014 you may be going too long on narrative; move to the laptop faster\"]}, {\"type\": \"caution\", \"label\": \"Caution\", \"content\": \"Do not cite specific revenue numbers as if they are this customer's data. Use 'industry benchmarks' language throughout. Do not promise specific FINRA compliance outcomes \\u2014 ServiceNow manages the workflow and orchestration around FINRA registration, not the registration itself. If asked about HRIS integration, acknowledge it is common and supported but is deliberately out of scope for this demo to keep the focus on HRSD native capabilities.\"}, {\"type\": \"transition\", \"label\": \"Transition\", \"content\": \"Now open your laptop. Say: 'Let me start where your advisors start \\u2014 with a question they have at 7pm that your service center cannot answer until 9am the next morning. Let me show you what that experience looks like today with Now Assist in the Employee Center.'\"}, {\"type\": \"painpoints\", \"label\": \"Pain Points Addressed\", \"items\": [\"6-8 week financial advisor onboarding delays suppress revenue generation per hire\", \"FINRA registration complexity creates manual tracking and compliance exposure\", \"HR service center overwhelmed with high-volume repetitive policy questions\", \"Slow onboarding increases recruit attrition risk before the first client meeting\"]}]",
